magazine limit of 15 rounds even more stringent than the 20 rounds 
sought in a bill pushed by sen howard metzenbaum dohio that also 
would ban many domestic weapons 
stephen e higgins director of the treasury departments bureau 
of alcohol tobacco and firearms said the permanent import ban on 
the 43 styles was required because the weapons did not meet the 
standards imposed by the gun control act of 1968 that law bars 
importation of weapons that are not used for legitimate sporting 
purposes 
lapierre said it takes only one complaint by one nra member that 
another member has violated the organizations bylaws to get a 
person considered for suspension or expulsion from the nra one 
bylaw requires that members protect and defend the constitution in 
particular the second amendment 
a single nra member can call for the expulsion of another member 
by alleging a violation of nra bylaws the groups ethics committee 
considers complaints 
if the committee recommends suspension or expulsion the member 
is given 30 days to request a hearing after a hearing the 
committees final recommendation is considered by the 75member nra 
board 
