the peace corps new program in hungary will 
involve about 60 american volunteers going there to train hungarians 
in the teaching of english agency officials said today 
president bush announced the program marking the first peace 
corps effort in a communist country during his visit to hungary 
in offering the corps volunteers bush said in budapest the 
teaching of english is one of the most popular american exports 
he said the program will help open the global market to more 
hungarians 
at a news conference here following bushs announcement peace 
corps director paul d coverdell declared that this is a historic 
day and the threshold of a new era for the united states peace 
corps 
when volunteers enter hungary it will be the 100th nation in 
which we have served he said it will also be the first 
european and first eastern bloc nation in which the peace corps has 
served 
coverdell said that while more than 121000 us volunteers have 
served in 99 developing countries over the last 28 years the 
program in hungary shows that the underlying mission of peace has no 
political or national boundaries 
president bush today told the hungarians that to succeed in 
reforms you need partners not just governments but people the 
united states peace corps is proud to provide some of those 
partners he said 
