the mother a 6weekold girl whose 
smothered body was found in a garbage can pleaded innocent today to 
murder in a case nearly identical to the death of the womans older 
child three years ago 
paula sims 30 was indicted tuesday by a madison county grand 
jury that still was weighing whether to charge her husband robert 
sims 37 in the slaying of their daughter heather said states 
attorney william haine 
wearing an orange jail jumpsuit and shackles mrs sims entered 
the courtroom of judge edward ferguson to hear the charges against 
her and have a written plea entered by attorney donald groshong 
a formal arraignment probably will be scheduled for next week 
said the judge who refused a motion that bond be set mrs sims is 
being held in madison county jail 
she faces the death penalty if convicted 
neither prosecutors nor groshong made any statement in court 
today 
the nude body of heather sims was found may 3 in a trash can 
across the mississippi river from the familys alton home four days 
after mrs sims reported that a masked gunman had abducted the girl 
it was an almost identical story she gave police three years 
earlier when her first daughter loralei disappeared 13 days after 
her birth in 1986 skeletal remains believed to be loraleis were 
found a few days later about 150 yards from the simses home in 
rural brighton in jersey county 
that death remains unsolved 
alton detective jody oguinn arrested mrs sims at her parents 
home in cottage hills shortly after the indictment was returned and 
led her away in handcuffs 
the grand jury heard more than four hours of testimony from her 
parents tuesday before returning the indictment they were ordered 
to testify after being granted immunity 
but the prosecutor said other evidence made the states case 
the physical evidence was very important haine said but he did 
not elaborate 
defense attorney groshong refused to comment 
but herb condray mrs sims brotherinlaw said police are only 
trying to save face by arresting her 
i think the police have egg on their face so bad that they 
would do anything condray said 
