<TEXT>
willie b zoo atlantas bachelor gorilla who 
spent nearly all of his life alone in a cage had his first outdoor 
romp with his new female companions today but preferred chewing a 
bamboo stalk to courtship 
zoo officials who hope to breed willie b said they werent 
surprised that romance didnt bloom immediately 
whether he will reproduce is still an open question said zoo 
director terry maple 
willie b came bounding out into his new naturalstyle habitat at 
about 9 am but spent most of the next hour or so snacking or 
mugging for a gaggle of photographers 
today is the first day in the rest of willie bs life as a 
social animal maple said 
sam winslow curator of mammals at the zoo said the chances of 
willie b mating are a long shot because he has been isolated in 
captivity so long 
he said zoo officials around the world cooperate in keeping 
breeding records and exchanging animals to keep an active gene pool 
going among the captive population and to avoid inbreeding 
he said it is most likely willie b would breed with the younger 
of his two companions kinyani age 6 who is just approaching 
maturity willie b is thought to be 31 
he had been introduced to female gorillas gradually over recent 
months and will be with them outdoors routinely from now on 
kinyani approached willie b briefly in their first few minutes 
outside together but scampered off a few yards which animal 
behaviorists said is normal 
the females are on loan from the yerkes regional primate research 
center of emory university willie b was caged from the time of his 
capture as an infant until his new outdoor habitat was completed a 
year ago 
