united states either doesnt have enough of or doesnt have at all 
some waste also is sent to canada because its plants are closer to 
where it originates 
some waste even hazardous waste contains metals that can be 
sold in other countries 
an internationl convention was signed in basel switzerland in 
march on the movement of hazardous waste it will become binding 
when 20 governments ratify it possibly next year 
the united states will decide soon whether to sign the agreement 
bernthal said 
bernthal objected to a bill that would require all international 
agreements to prohibit us exports unless the importing country has 
provisions for dealing with it that are as strict as us 
requirements 
there is no international consensus that one particular method 
of disposing of wastes is the only method which protects human 
health and the environment he said 
hajost suggested that the bill should allow the government to 
stop exports if it has reason to believe that the waste will not be 
handled properly in the importing country 
