that year and the draft plan simply pushed that back one day to 
jan 1 2001 
the 9millionton sulfur dioxide reduction is used in the draft 
because the administration is counting the 1millionton reduction 
already achieved by smelting plants according to rosenberg 
responding to another criticism from the environmental side 
rosenberg said draft language requiring consideration of economic 
costs in ordering reduced toxic chemical emissions was always bushs 
goal 
