problem with violent crime sasser said it will provide a 
rigorous test for the police corps concept 
the measure envisions bringing the nations total police force to 
580000 within four years of the programs implementation 
the cost is projected to rise each year as the program builds 
from 50 million in 1990 to 290 million in 1992 and more later 
specter said 
the measure has the support of the national fraternal order of 
police and the national association of police organizations which 
represents 90000 rankandfile officers 
other senate sponsors include democrats joseph lieberman of 
connecticut bill bradley of new jersey john kerry of 
massachusetts harry reid of nevada and republicans warren rudman 
of new hampshire and trent lott of mississippi 
