holds the leningrad job that put him there 
voters in leningrad the countrys secondlargest city rejected 
virtually their entire party leadership in the march parliamentary 
elections solovyovs defeat was especially embarrassing because he 
ran unopposed and still could not win approval from 50 percent of 
the voters in this city of about 48 million people 
