wirths bill would 
reimpose limits on advertising time in childrens tv shows that 
the federal communications commission repealed in 1984 those limits 
are 95 minutes of commercials per hour on weekends and 12 minutes 
per hour during weekdays 
reclassify socalled programlength commercials as 
advertisements thereby effectively eliminating them 
require broadcasters to give advance public notice of programs 
designed specifically to educate and inform children 
