tropical storm barry formed wednesday in the open 
atlantic and carried top winds of 40 mph as it marched slowly 
northward forecasters said 
at 1030 pm edt wednesday barry was near latitude 243 north 
longtitude 551 west about 675 miles northeast of the northern 
leeward islands in the lesser antilles 
barry which was moving to the northwest earlier turned sharply 
to the north wednesday night at 6 mph and posed no threat to land 
said forecaster hal gerrish at the national hurricane center in 
suburban coral gables 
