<TEXT>
like any car that has been around for a decade the mazda rx7 
has changed the car is wider and more expensive the outside 
styling is more rounded and the rx7 has been transformed from a 
spirited scooter to a more substantial sports car 
but thankfully some of the best features remain the durable 
smooth rotary engine the sporty handling and nimble responsiveness 
and the reardrive design 
the performance of the mazda rx7 gtus test car clearly showed 
that many of the selective changes over the years have helped keep 
the rx7 a viable competitor in the sports car field 
the engine in the test car teamed with fivespeed manual 
transmission started easily and worked smoothly in both city and 
highway driving the gtus is not the fastest sports car around with 
a rating of 77 seconds to go from 0 to 60 mph but it had plenty of 
good steady zip and theres a higherpriced turbocharged rx7 
model that offers even quicker acceleration 
i also appreciated the fact that the reardrive design meant 
there was no torque steer under hard acceleration as there is in so 
many frontdrive sporty cars though i noticed that the test car 
gulped down the fuel i was impressed by the highrevving rotary 
engine especially knowing it has earned a reputation for 
reliability 
a mazda spokesman noted that rx7s have done extraordinarily 
well in endurancerelated racing consumer reports also ranks 
highly the rx7s of the 198287 model years they consistently 
earned a much better than average label in the magazines survey of 
car owners 
the mazda spokesman mentioned the loyalty among many rx7 owners 
with about 41000 members the rx7 clubs around the country are 
rank as one of the largest collection of clubs honoring a single car 
marque 
fit and finish on the test car was superb the ventilation system 
was powerful and the seats redesigned for 1989 with more lateral 
support were firm and sturdy which i appreciated as i got 
accustomed to the cars hard sporty ride 
