because of increased competition from sporty coupes that offer 
seating for more than two passengers and partly because of rising 
insurance costs sales of the rx7 have been declining they hit 
56205 in 1986 then fell to 38345 in 1987 and 27814 in 1988 
mazda said sales of about 20000 are expected this year 
because of the increase in insurance costs some buyers are being 
quoted prices for insurance on their sports cars that are higher 
than their monthly car payments a mazda spokesman said 
