fannie mae reported wednesday that earnings 
soared 60 percent in the second quarter as yields increased on its 
mortgage portfolio and fee income rose 
fannie mae formally known as the federal national mortgage 
association is a congressionally chartered shareholderowned 
company that provides money for homebuyers by purchasing mortgages 
from lenders and packaging them into securities for sale to 
investors 
fannie maes earnings totaled 1930 million or 228 per share 
on interest income of 27 billion for the three months ended june 
30 that compared with a profit of 1207 million or 153 a share 
on interest income of 254 billion in the 1988 quarter 
for the first six months of 1989 fannie mae earned 3582 
million or 427 per share on total interest income of 535 
billion the same period last year fannie mae earned 2216 million 
or 282 a share on total interest income of 498 billion 
fannie mae president roger birk attributed the sharp rise in 
secondquarter earnings to a widening in the spread between the 
interest the company earns on its investment portfolio and what it 
pays on its debt 
another factor was an increase in income from fees charged 
lenders for guaranteeing morgage backed securities he said 
fannie mae purchased 45 billion in mortgages in the second 
quarter up from 34 billion in the first but down from 69 
billion a year ago 
