<TEXT>
communications giant gannett co inc said 
wednesday its secondquarter earnings rose 17 percent partly because 
newspaper advertising revenues were up while production costs were 
down 
aftertax profit for the three months ended june 25 was 1121 
million or 70 cents a share on operating revenues of 9041 
million that compared with earnings of 975 million or 60 cents a 
share on operating revenues of 8469 million for the same quarter 
in 1988 
operating income advanced 15 percent in the second quarter to 
2155 million from 1881 million last year 
gannetts chairman and president john j curley said second 
quarter earnings for the rosslyn vabased newspaper broadcasting 
and outdoor advertising concern were fueled by higher newspaper 
operating income 
newspaper earnings benefitted from higher advertising revenues 
lower newsprint prices and the firstever secondquarter profit at 
usa today gannetts national newspaper curley said in a letter 
to shareholders 
usa todays first profitable quarter came in the last quarter of 
1987 
first half profits for 1989 were up 9 percent to 187 million or 
116 per share compared to 1714 million or 106 a share last 
year 
revenues also were up 7 percent to 17 billion from 16 billion 
in the first half of last year 
gannett which operates in 41 states the district of columbia 
and seven overseas locations publishes 84 daily newspapers 
operates 10 television and 16 radio stations gannett news services 
and the largest outdoor advertising company in north america 
</TEXT>
